<h2>Collection of mathematical chess problem</h2>
<p>
	Along the years, I collected some mathematically inspired chess problems and created a few activities around chess and mathematics. I am trying to keep them all in one place. 
	You can find them in a draft of a booklet below. Feel free to have a look; contact me if you want to contribute, or if you have comments. It will take some time before it is final, if it ever
	becomes finalised, but I will try to update it from time to time when I find new problems  
</p>
<h3>Current version: 01 from 2022-04-06</h3>	
<p>	
	<a href="/popularization/echecs/2022-04_ALR_Queens_of_the_chessboards.pdf">Queens of the chessboards</a>. 
</p>

